Exercise 1

# Do some preliminary investigations & cleaning

diamonds %>%
  filter(length_mm > 0 | width_mm > 0 | depth_mm > 0) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_length = mean(length_mm),
    mean_width = mean(width_mm),
    mean_depth = mean(depth_mm),
    mean_depth_pct = mean(depth_pct)
  ) 
## # A tibble: 1  4
##   mean_length mean_width mean_depth mean_depth_pct
##         <dbl>      <dbl>      <dbl>          <dbl>
## 1        5.73       5.74       3.54           61.7
diamonds %>%
  ggplot(mapping = 
           aes(
             x = length_mm,
             y = depth_pct,
             colour = cut
             )) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5)

diamonds %>%
  ggplot(mapping = 
           aes(
             x = width_mm,
             y = depth_pct,
             colour = cut
             )) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5)

diamonds %>%
  ggplot(mapping = 
           aes(
             x = depth_mm,
             y = depth_pct,
             colour = cut
             )) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5)

Exercise 2

diamonds <- diamonds %>%
  mutate(table_mm = table_pct * width_mm / 100)

# Overall table_mm arithmetic mean?

diamonds %>%
  summarise(mean_table_length = mean(table_mm))
## # A tibble: 1  1
##   mean_table_length
##               <dbl>
## 1              3.30
# table_mm arithmetic mean within each clarity category

diamonds %>%
  group_by(clarity ) %>%
  summarise(mean_table_length = mean(table_mm))
## # A tibble: 8  2
##   clarity mean_table_length

Exercise 4

# Write gmean() command
gmean <- function(x){
  return(sum(log(x)) ^ 1/length(x))
}
